               <p>MR. ELLIS conducted the Prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340515-75-person763">
                  WILLIAM 
                  DREW
               <interp inst="t18340515-75-person763" type="surname" value="DREW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340515-75-person763" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340515-75-person763" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (City police-constable No. 88). On the <rs id="t18340515-75-cd424" type="crimeDate">29th of April</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340515-75-off423 t18340515-75-cd424"></join>, about half-past two o'clock in the afternoon, I saw the prisoner in Fetter-lane in company with another person - they went down King's-head-court towards Holborn - I went with Serjeant Waller into <placeName id="t18340515-75-crimeloc425">Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340515-75-crimeloc425" type="placeName" value="Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340515-75-crimeloc425" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340515-75-off423 t18340515-75-crimeloc425"></join> - we took hold of the prisoner, and asked if he had any thing about him - he said "No" - we took him into a hosier's shop, and found half-a-crown in his waistcoat pocket - he said he had picked it up - we asked him if he had any more - he said "No" - we desired him to take off his shoes and<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183405150049"></xptr>coat, and in the sleeve of the coat we found three more counterfeit half-crowns - he said he picked them up - we asked why he divided them - he said because he did not wish the person he was with, to know that he picked up more than one.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340515-75-person764">
                  CHARLES 
                  WALLER
               <interp inst="t18340515-75-person764" type="surname" value="WALLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340515-75-person764" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340515-75-person764" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (City police-serjeant No. 8). I was present - what had been stated is true.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340515-75-person765">
                  JOHN 
                  FIELD
               <interp inst="t18340515-75-person765" type="surname" value="FIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340515-75-person765" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340515-75-person765" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am inspector of counterfeit coin to his Majesty's Mint - these four half-crowns are all counterfeit, and cast in the same mould.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked them up, and if my companion had asked what I had got, I meant to have said one half-crown, and to have kept the other three to myself.</p>
               <p>
